    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-05-13</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-06-02T21:30:57Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Veterans' Group Life Insurance Improvement Act of 2009 - Allows veterans insured under Veterans' Group Life Insurance, no more than once in each five-year period, to increase such coverage amount if: (1) the veteran is under 60 years of age; (2) the increase is not more than $25,000; and (3) the total amount of such insurance does not exceed $400,000 (the limit authorized for a veteran under Servicemembers' Group Life Insurance).</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
